message.content:
Excellent! Windows 3.11 is running at 1024x768 graphics mode with a proper desktop! The colors (light gray, white, dark gray, light blue, black) match the Windows 3.11 Program Manager. Let me finalize the setup.

{
  "analysis": "Windows 3.11 is successfully booted to the desktop at 1024x768 graphics mode. Colors match Windows 3.11 Program Manager: gray desktop (192,192,192), white (255,255,255), dark gray (128,128,128), blue title bar (167,200,240), black (0,0,0). Need to save screenshot, verify all services, and confirm keyboard input works.",
  "plan": "1. Save the desktop screenshot as PNG. 2. Verify all services are running (VNC, nginx, monitor socket). 3. Test keyboard input via monitor socket. 4. Confirm everything is properly configured.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "convert /tmp/win-mode2.ppm /tmp/win311-desktop.png && ls -la /tmp/win311-desktop.png\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ps aux | grep -E 'qemu|nginx|websockify' | grep -v grep\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ss -tlnp | grep -E '5901|6080|:80'\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la /tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'sendkey a' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'info status' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' http://localhost:80/\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
